parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Leading to Fire
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause a fire in the engine compartment, potentially leading to vehicle damage, injury, or even death.
symptoms: Illumination of all lights on the instrument panel

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake system failure can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Loud grinding noise when applying brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overcurrent at the ABS controller voltage conductor can cause a fire in the engine compartment, potentially leading to vehicle damage, injury, or even death.
The engine performance issues can cause a rough idle, potentially leading to decreased fuel efficiency, increased emissions, and engine damage.
The failure of the magnetic switch in the starter motor can cause the vehicle to not start when hot, and in extreme cases, can lead to a fire hazard due to the solenoid shorting out.
symptoms: The vehicle does not start when hot
the starter motor does not turn
the vehicle has a no-start condition.
